riants/000/115/616/4e2016543ea3e299dcadd088be7d0225de3419e0_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1955774,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Is 'Downloads' the default location for downloading on fresh install? \n\nAlso FWIW, I'm not sure if Brave is 'broken' in a good way as far as webkitdirectory because there is a much more severe problem with it on Chrome that doesn't seem to work on Brave. \nhttp://leucosite.com/Chrome-Firefox-Edge-Local-File-Disclosure/\n\nIf you run the PoC at the end, you should be loading entire folders alongside their files (on Chrome). But for some reason Brave only loads a reference to the folder and nothing else. In case this will be 'fixed' in the future, it should be considered. ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-08-25T21:14:35.461Z","updated_at":"2017-08-25T21:14:35.461Z","actor":{"username":"qab","cleared":true,"url":"/qab","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1956041,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"It turns out this is because we are using Electron's implementation of file picker, not Chrome's. We have an open issue to migrate to Chrome's file picker: https://github.com/brave/muon/issues/242. I am going to close this Hacker1 issue since the underlying problem is already logged in github.\n\nThanks for alerting us to the folder loading vulnerability in Chrome. I agree it is more serious and we should try to do something to avoid it when we migrate.","automated_resp